I now have a complete understanding of the codebase. Here is the full implementation plan.

---

## Runtime Theme Switching Implementation Plan

### 1. Full Color Token Audit and Mapping

I traced every color SCSS variable across all 19 SCSS files. Here is the complete inventory of current SCSS color variables and how they map to the user's 5-token palette:

**Current SCSS color variables (15 color tokens + 4 glass + 5 shadows):**

| Current SCSS Variable | Semantic Role | Maps to User Token |
|---|---|---|
| `$bgDeep` (#0a0a0f) | Deepest background | `bg` |
| `$bgBase` (#12121a) | Base background | derived from `bg` |
| `$bgElevated` (#1a1a2e) | Elevated surfaces | `structure` |
| `$bgSurface` (#22223a) | Card/panel surfaces | `surface` |
| `$textPrimary` (#f0f0f5) | Primary text | `text` |
| `$textSecondary` (#8888a0) | Secondary text | derived from `text` |
| `$textMuted` (#55556a) | Muted/placeholder | derived from `text` |
| `$accentPurple` (#6c5ce7) | Primary accent | `accent` |
| `$accentPurpleLight` (#8b7cf0) | Lighter accent variant | derived from `accent` |
| `$accentPurpleDark` (#5a4bd6) | Darker accent variant | derived from `accent` |
| `$accentTeal` (#00cec9) | Secondary accent | new token: `accent2` |
| `$accentTealLight` (#33ddd9) | Secondary accent light | derived from `accent2` |
| `$danger` (#ff6b6b) | Error/danger | stays semantic (non-themed or themed) |
| `$success` (#00b894) | Success state | stays semantic |
| `$warning` (#fdcb6e) | Warning state | stays semantic |
| `$glassBg` | Glass background | derived from `text` (white at low alpha) |
| `$glassBgHover` | Glass hover bg | derived from `text` (white at low alpha) |
| `$glassBorder` | Glass border | derived from `text` (white at low alpha) |
| `$glassBorderHover` | Glass hover border | derived from `text` (white at low alpha) |
| `$shadowSm/Md/Lg/Glow` | Accent-colored shadows | derived from `accent` |
| `$shadowTealGlow` | Secondary glow | derived from `accent2` |

**Design decision: Expand from 5 to 7 base tokens.** The user requested 5 (`bg`, `structure`, `surface`, `accent`, `text`), but the codebase also uses a secondary accent color (`$accentTeal`) extensively in gradients, badges, and the logo. We need a 6th token `accent2` (secondary accent) and derived tokens computed via CSS `color-mix()` and alpha channels. Semantic colors (`danger`, `success`, `warning`) should remain constant across themes or get their own optional overrides.

### 2. CSS Custom Property Token System

**File: `C:\Users\yakik\Documents\projects\rearden\apps\web\src\styles\_tokens.scss` (NEW)**

This new file defines the complete CSS custom property set. Create it as a central token definition file.

```scss
// _tokens.scss - CSS Custom Property token definitions for theming
// Each theme defines 7 base tokens; all others are derived.

// ==========================================
// Y2K Theme (default)
// ==========================================
:root,
[data-theme="y2k"] {
  // --- Base tokens (7 user-defined) ---
  --color-bg: #0E1A1F;
  --color-structure: #1C3240;
  --color-surface: #3A6B5C;
  --color-accent: #C8F000;
  --color-accent2: #00E5CC;       // secondary accent (teal equivalent)
  --color-text: #E8F0EE;
  --color-danger: #ff6b6b;
  --color-success: #00b894;
  --color-warning: #fdcb6e;

  // --- Derived: backgrounds ---
  --color-bg-base: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-bg) 70%, var(--color-structure) 30%);
  --color-bg-elevated: var(--color-structure);
  --color-bg-surface: var(--color-surface);

  // --- Derived: text ---
  --color-text-primary: var(--color-text);
  --color-text-secondary: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-text) 55%, var(--color-bg) 45%);
  --color-text-muted: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-text) 35%, var(--color-bg) 65%);

  // --- Derived: accent ---
  --color-accent-light: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 75%, white 25%);
  --color-accent-dark: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 80%, black 20%);
  --color-accent2-light: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent2) 75%, white 25%);

  // --- Glass (uses light overlay on dark themes) ---
  --glass-bg: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
  --glass-bg-hover: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
  --glass-border: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
  --glass-border-hover: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12);
  --glass-blur: 12px;

  // --- Shadows (accent-derived) ---
  --shadow-sm: 0 2px 8px color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 8%, transparent 92%);
  --shadow-md: 0 4px 16px color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 12%, transparent 88%);
  --shadow-lg: 0 8px 32px color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 16%, transparent 84%);
  --shadow-glow: 0 0 20px color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 30%, transparent 70%);
  --shadow-accent2-glow: 0 0 20px color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent2) 30%, transparent 70%);

  // --- Focus ring ---
  --focus-ring-color: var(--color-accent);

  // --- Selection ---
  --selection-bg: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 30%, transparent 70%);
}

// ==========================================
// Purple Night Theme
// ==========================================
[data-theme="purple-night"] {
  --color-bg: #0a0a0f;
  --color-structure: #1a1a2e;
  --color-surface: #22223a;
  --color-accent: #6c5ce7;
  --color-accent2: #00cec9;
  --color-text: #f0f0f5;
  --color-danger: #ff6b6b;
  --color-success: #00b894;
  --color-warning: #fdcb6e;

  --color-bg-base: #12121a;
  --color-bg-elevated: var(--color-structure);
  --color-bg-surface: var(--color-surface);

  --color-text-primary: var(--color-text);
  --color-text-secondary: #8888a0;
  --color-text-muted: #55556a;

  --color-accent-light: #8b7cf0;
  --color-accent-dark: #5a4bd6;
  --color-accent2-light: #33ddd9;

  --glass-bg: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
  --glass-bg-hover: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
  --glass-border: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
  --glass-border-hover: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12);
  --glass-blur: 12px;

  --shadow-sm: 0 2px 8px rgba(108, 92, 231, 0.08);
  --shadow-md: 0 4px 16px rgba(108, 92, 231, 0.12);
  --shadow-lg: 0 8px 32px rgba(108, 92, 231, 0.16);
  --shadow-glow: 0 0 20px rgba(108, 92, 231, 0.3);
  --shadow-accent2-glow: 0 0 20px rgba(0, 206, 201, 0.3);

  --focus-ring-color: var(--color-accent);
  --selection-bg: rgba(108, 92, 231, 0.3);
}
```

**Why `color-mix()` for the Y2K theme and explicit values for Purple Night:** The Purple Night theme preserves exact current hex values. For Y2K (and future themes), `color-mix()` derives secondary/muted shades automatically from the 7 base tokens, making it trivial to add new themes: just define 7 base colors and the derived set recalculates. `color-mix(in srgb, ...)` has 96%+ browser support and works with CSS custom properties. For the Purple Night theme, explicit values ensure pixel-perfect backward compatibility with the current look.

**Fallback note:** If `color-mix()` is a concern, all derived values can be pre-computed as explicit hex values per theme. The plan works either way.

### 3. Bridge File for SCSS Consumption

**File: `C:\Users\yakik\Documents\projects\rearden\apps\web\src\styles\_variables.scss` (MODIFY)**

Replace the color SCSS variables with CSS custom property references. Non-color variables (spacing, radii, typography, transitions, breakpoints, layout) remain untouched.

```scss
