// Colors — now referencing CSS custom properties
// =============================================
$bgDeep: var(--color-bg);
$bgBase: var(--color-bg-base);
$bgElevated: var(--color-bg-elevated);
$bgSurface: var(--color-bg-surface);

$textPrimary: var(--color-text-primary);
$textSecondary: var(--color-text-secondary);
$textMuted: var(--color-text-muted);

$accentPurple: var(--color-accent);
$accentPurpleLight: var(--color-accent-light);
$accentPurpleDark: var(--color-accent-dark);
$accentTeal: var(--color-accent2);
$accentTealLight: var(--color-accent2-light);

$danger: var(--color-danger);
$success: var(--color-success);
$warning: var(--color-warning);

// Glass
$glassBg: var(--glass-bg);
$glassBgHover: var(--glass-bg-hover);
$glassBorder: var(--glass-border);
$glassBorderHover: var(--glass-border-hover);
$glassBlur: 12px; // stays static — blur amount doesn't need to theme

// Shadows
$shadowSm: var(--shadow-sm);
$shadowMd: var(--shadow-md);
$shadowLg: var(--shadow-lg);
$shadowGlow: var(--shadow-glow);
$shadowTealGlow: var(--shadow-accent2-glow);

// =============================================
// Spacing, Radii, Typography, etc. — unchanged
// =============================================
// ... (all existing non-color vars stay exactly as they are)
```

**This is the key insight that minimizes per-component changes.** By redefining the SCSS variables as `var(--custom-property)`, every component that already uses `$bgDeep`, `$accentPurple`, etc. will automatically switch to CSS custom properties with ZERO changes to their SCSS files -- as long as they only use these variables in standard CSS property values (not in SCSS functions).

### 4. The `rgba()` Problem -- Files That Need Manual Edits

The strategy above works for direct property assignments like `color: $accentPurple`. But SCSS `rgba($accentPurple, 0.3)` will **break** when `$accentPurple` is `var(--color-accent)` because SCSS `rgba()` expects a color value at compile time, not a CSS variable.

